<br>
ok got that out of my system.<br>
<br>
One of the biggest challenges that I have in game as a tradeskiller is getting materials for the tradeskills.  I can farm with Von or Muratt but I hate the loss of exp to someone who could use it.  I also think its a waste to go around hitting spiderlings for 56 pts of damage and then haveing my fluxblade axe proc for 150 on top of that.<br>
<br>
This will be great for me in that I have characters from lv 16 to lv 55 and I will now be able to go into a win win situation.  I wont be farming anymore.  I can sellect the character that will get exp and then get the materials I need with them.<br>
<br>
Im kinda indifferent about the buff thing.  My 2 main toons are over lv 45 and the ones under are primarily tank/melee type anyway.  Im not saying that aego or c3 doesnt help but the down side is that we are now getting a proliferation of the &quot;greedy caster&quot; types that the game can do without.<br>
<br>
I offer up Cam as an example of the OPPOSITE of this.  I see him casting C3 in pok mostly and have never seen him turn someone away because their &quot;donation&quot; was too small.  I have seen others turn people away and have been turned away for not haveing a big enough donation.  Others set minimum donation levels in order for them to cast a buff.  For spells with material components I can understand (hehe paid 1.2k for dots on the first big raid i lead) but c3, potg, and most shammy buffs dont have material components.<br>
<br>
The primary loss in this &quot;no uber buffs for those under lv 45&quot; is gonna be to people like me who have a low tolerance for idiots.  I would rather solo my lv 24 chanter than get in a group with a player that repeatedly breaks my mezzes and whines about waiting for me to med up. (hehe ask stragus in game what we do to people that repeatedly break mezes.  can you say &quot;death touch&quot;? I knew you could.)  I am gonna have a slower turn around time for mana in my casters and as a result I will level slower.  This might be learning the class but for me its translates into more time to do housework while i med.  There are only so many games of gems that i can play and still keep my sanity.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cp<br>
